ular density, and ionization\nparameter), and derived formulae that can be used to compute Se and Kr ICFs. In\nthe second paper of this series, we will apply these ICFs to our full sample of\n120 PNe, which comprises the first large-scale survey of n-capture elements in\nPNe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Nov 2006 18:36:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
